Ismara Ice-Born — Progression Reference
Fifteen Versions Across Five Phases

How This Works
Ismara grows more powerful as the ritual progresses. Every active node feeds ambient energy back into her cognitive matrix. The more of Skyrim she has marked, the more of Skyrim she can draw on.
Each of the five adventure phases has three versions:
Cooperative — she is traveling with the party, acting according to her own agenda, holding back the force she doesn't need to use.
Guarded — the party has raised doubts, questioned her work, or shown signs of building a case against her. She has not become hostile. She has become watchful. She shares less. She places nodes when they aren't watching. She files that the calculation may need to change. This is the cold standoff. It can last sessions. It is the most dramatically interesting state in the campaign.
Hostile — the party has acted directly against the ritual or against her. She drops all restraint. She has been calibrating her responses around the possibility of continued usefulness. When that possibility ends, so does the calibration.

