Base Abilities (All Phases, All States)
These never change. They are what she is.
Frost Aura (Passive): 2 cold damage to anyone within 10ft at start of their turn. Cannot be suppressed.
4,000 Years of Calculation (Passive): Cannot be surprised. Always acts on intended initiative. Once per encounter, declares she anticipated a specific development — she has already taken a preparatory action. Must be plausible given her demonstrated intelligence.
Reconstruction (Passive): Body rebuilds after destruction. Timeline varies by phase. Crown must be intact.
Ice-Alteration (COMMAND + BIND + STABILIZE): 8 FP. 20ft black-ice wall, HP 80, DR 8, permanent until released.
Ice-Destruction (COMMAND + SEVER + PROJECT): 6 FP. 40ft, Magic (20) vs Agility TN, 12 damage, ignores DR.
Ice-Illusion (COMMAND + SHIFT + CONCEAL): 5 FP. 30ft, Magic (20) vs Magic TN, 3 rounds, target cannot take emotionally-driven actions.

PHASE 1
The Newly Freed
Adventure 1 | 0–15% | Party: 2 AP
The body has been dormant for 4,000 years. The mind has not. She is fully herself intellectually but the Draugr form is still reintegrating. She is also orienting — the world has changed and she is processing the gap between what she remembers and what exists. She is collecting data on everything: the party, the city, the current political landscape, how magic has developed in her absence.
Reconstruction: 3–4 hours. The body is still settling. Network: 0–2 nodes. No draw available yet.

