The cold standoff: The most tense version. They have been through five holds together. There are things they have chosen not to say to each other. She has been showing them what she wanted them to see and now she has stopped showing them anything. The party is looking at her differently. She is looking at them the way she looks at a problem she is deciding whether to solve.
Return to Cooperative: Possible but difficult. The Khajiit is the only path. It requires something that costs the Khajiit something — not a clever argument, not a promise, something that puts the Khajiit at disadvantage in her calculation and she accepts it anyway. That is what it takes to pull her back from here.

