What changes from Cooperative:
She does not deliver the Riften revelation in Guarded state. She has been building to telling them what the ritual does to the nodes — that moment is her final act of regard for the party as people she travels with rather than obstacles she manages. If she has moved to Guarded, she has decided they are not people she trusts with that information. She does not tell them. They reach Adventure 5 not knowing, from her, what happens to the frozen people.
This has narrative consequences. A party that goes into Adventure 5 not knowing — because they moved to Guarded before Riften — experiences the transfer differently than one that was told. They may find out from other sources. They may not find out until it's happening.
Geographic Awareness is now tactically constant. She knows where the party is relative to her at all times in node-dense holds. She cannot be surprised. She cannot be separated from information about their movements.
Pre-building is extensive now. Every location she has spent more than 30 minutes in has been measured and thought through. She has been here before in her mind. Many times.
The cold standoff: Almost over. She is very close to the ritual's completion. The calculation on whether they are an asset or a threat is near resolution. She is patient. She has always been patient. But she is running a timeline now and patience is becoming expensive.
Return to Cooperative: Still technically possible. Barely. The Khajiit would have to do something that costs them considerably. She would return but she would be different — cooperative in behavior but with something closed behind it that was open before. Not all the way back. Enough.

