This is the mortal limit.
A 5 AP party of 6 that triggers Phase 4 Hostile in a straight fight will lose. Not probably. The math does not support them. If this happens, either the table needs a solution that has nothing to do with the combat system, or they are experiencing the consequence of a decision they made.
Changes from Phase 4 Cooperative:
Network Channel in Round 1. Effectively 44 FP.
Ice-Destruction: +2 damage (16 total, ignores DR).
Skyrim's Cold used offensively and deliberately. She positions for maximum coverage on every use.
Geographic Awareness: she cannot be flanked, ambushed, or approached unseen near any node. In Adventure 4 territory, that is most of Skyrim.
Ice-Illusion on the Khajiit first if they are present and opposing her. She cannot stop this. She does it and the conflict in her processing is visible to anyone watching her. She does it anyway.
What winning looks like: Not killing her. Surviving. Reaching Adventure 5 with the resonance disruption knowledge. That is the win condition. The fight is not.

PHASE 5
The Transfer Begins
Adventure 5 | 90–100% | Party: 5–6 AP
45–50 nodes across eight to nine holds. The Eye of Magnus is the only missing component. She can feel the shape of the whole ritual. She can feel what it will mean when it completes. She is not yet the continent but she is close enough to feel its edges.
There is no more persuasion in any state. There is no more patience with arguments. The time for arguments was Adventures 1 through 4.
Reconstruction: 30 minutes anywhere within the network. The land is already partly hers. Network Channel: Recovers 16 FP. Skyrim's Cold: 12 cold damage to all in 40ft radius. Twice per encounter. New Passive — The Land Knows: Aware of all living beings within the College of Winterhold and surrounding mile. Cannot be surprised anywhere within network range. The "4,000 Years" passive is now absolute and geographic. New Passive — Transfer State: While connected to the Eye, she cannot take Move actions. She is stationary. She has built the College around this fact. New Passive — The Resonance Window: During transfer, Crown DR drops to 0. Brief. Malleable. This is the only window in which the disruption is possible.
